Steven Gerrard has insisted that Luis Suarez was the best player he played alongside at Liverpool. The Aston Villa boss spent three-and-a-half seasons with Suarez at Anfield during which time the Uruguayan was one of the most prolific strikers in Europe. He scored an impressive 82 goals and notched a further 47 assists in 133 appearances for the club before he left for Barcelona in 2014. Arsenal Set To Offer Arteta New Contract Before End Of Season Police Recruitment: PSC Expresses Concern Over Low Enrollment Of… The 34-year-old’s future has been the subject of much speculation with his contract at Atletico Madrid set to expire in the summer, and he has been linked with sensational move to Villa Park.  Gerrard has already brought back another former teammate from his time at Anfield in Philippe Coutinho and revealed the esteem he still holds Suarez in. When asked in an interview with Sky Sports who was the greatest player he played with at Liverpool, the Villa boss chose the Uruguay star ahead of Fernando Torres. “It would probably be between Torres and Suarez. POLL “But if I was forced because Luis did it over a longer period of time, and he left for a foreign club rather than Chelsea, I’d go for Luis Suarez.”